THE BOTTOM LINE:
With a No-trump stopper such as A x facing x x, unless the suit might be divided 7-2, do not hold up, particularly when a low card is led. 

It is not always easy for the opening leader to read your weakness if you win the ace. |
PG| ***** 214 ***** |


NT|^B@2
For example, if East plays the @SK and West has @SQ 10 x x (x), West cannot be sure who has the jack. In the actual diagram, West can't be sure who has the king. |
